  <summary>10/9/1997--Introduced.
Religious Freedom Peace Tax Fund Act - Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to establish in the Treasury the Religious Freedom Peace Tax Fund into which shall be deposited taxes paid by designated conscientious objectors. Requires and expresses the sense of the Congress that deposits in the Fund be allocated annually for any non-military appropriation. Sets forth reporting requirements.</summary>
